{
  "stem": "20021.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Later, of course, I wouldn't, after bar mitzvah in particular.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So, you know, you were expected to-- to follow the prayers most of the time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there was-- twice a week, I would also go to a synagogue to get a lesson in the Talmud from somebody, a selected rabbi who would teach the Talmud.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So basically, that's-- it was strictly observant, much more than you say you find today in Europe or in America or throughout the world.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Shabbos would start, of course, with my mother lighting the candles.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then me and my father and my brother would go to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When we would come back from the synagogue, my father would make kiddush.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then throughout the meal, we would sing occasional songs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was not just eating the meal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was eating and stopping and singing certain songs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One of the songs which I remember was primarily to glorify the role of the woman, my mother, you know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There's a special song like that called 'Eishet Chayil.'",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] I'm not a good singer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But basically what it says is 'Eishet Chayil' means who is lucky the man who finds the woman who is [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the great accomplisher, in other words, that the woman's role in the family is very crucial and-- and she's more-- a treasure more than pearls.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's more or less the song.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's taken out of the-- of the part of the Bible, which is called [NON-ENGLISH], which is ascribed to King Solomon.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, during Shabbos, of course, no work was done.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was truly a day of rest.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
